case_circumstances: Human remains of a female (caucasian skeletal characteristics with possible afro-american genetic admixture) were discovered on September 1, 1996 in rural Polk County, Oregon.  No clothing was associated with the remains.  The decedent had a crescent-shaped healed cranial scar on her frontal bone (forehead), indicating she had been the subject of a successful past craniotomy surgery.  This surgery would NOT have left a scar on the skin of her forehead, although the healed crescent shape may have been seen through the skin as an indentation or depression.
